definition[0]: a short high sound made by a piece of electronic equipment
definition[1]: to make a high electronic sound
example[0]: The timer on the cooker started to bleep.
definition[2]: to let someone know, through their bleeper, that you want them to telephone you
definition[3]: to prevent an offensive word being heard on television or the radio by making a high electronic sound
example[1]: All the swear words had been bleeped out.
